# Design System & UI Stability Rules

## 1. Design Tokens (The 5-Color Palette)
>
> Use these semantic classes to maintain theme consistency across Landing and Mission pages.

1. `primary`: Main Action buttons and active UI states. (`bg-primary`)
2. `secondary`: Success indicators or secondary "Learn More" actions. (`text-secondary`)
3. `accent`: High-attention callouts, "New" badges, or alerts. (`text-accent`)
4. `highlight`: Unique UI elements, special links, or featured icons. (`text-highlight`)
5. `surface`: Secondary section backgrounds to create visual separation. (`bg-surface`)

## 2. Anti-Clash Spacing Rules

- **The Outer Limit:** All content MUST be wrapped in `<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">`.
- **Vertical Breathing:** Every major section MUST use `py-16 md:py-24`.
- **Internal Spacing:** Use `space-y-6` for headers/paragraphs to prevent text clumping.

## 3. Implementation Constraints

- **Typography:** Use `font-heading` for all titles and `font-sans` for body/labels.
- **Box Rules:** Never apply a `border` without at least `p-6` (Padding) to prevent text from touching edges.
- **Interactive:** All buttons require `transition-all active:scale-95`.

## 4. Plug & Play Hero Template

